  "texts": [
    "X-rays and CT scans are the most commonly used anatomic imaging modalities for detecting and diagnosing various lung diseases [6].ML has significantly impacted medical imaging, and there has been substantial progress in applying ML-based detection approaches and algorithms.",
    "ML can diagnose lung disorders using images from medical or radiological procedures [10].",
    "ML, a subfield of artificial intelligence (AI), tries to make computers learn from data [11].",
    "Consequently, ML offers an automated framework that may be utilized to detect or anticipate lung illnesses in their earliest stages compared to manual methods [12].Identifying prominent lung conditions such as Pneumonia, Lung cancer, and COVID-19 using imaging and ML encounters some impediments:• The intricate characteristics of lung structures and the overlapping patterns of diseases might result in misinterpretations.",
    "• Various imaging methods may lead to differences in the quality and consistency of data."
  ]
}